<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> For you, Applicant = someone in the Trial period<br>
For us Appicant = someone Inquireing about getting a trail period.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
For us, Applicant is someone who emails an app and we discuss whether we want them on raids. They become invites if they pass that stage and in due time can become sponsors or get the boot. We make it difficult to become a member becuase  many apps get the &quot;OMG i just killed everything, i win Luclin!&quot; complex then quit the game after a few weeks of raiding with us.  sometimes you can spot that a mile away and other times its harder. <br>
<br>
So apps come and go and occasionally the serious gamer comes along and shows he intends to be around for more than a few clearings. those are the people we want. The ones who actually care about helping the guild and themselves advance. <br>
<br>
There are some decent powergamers on this server who are trapped in lower tier guilds mainly out of obligation , they want to be the best and kick that ass everyday but dont want to leave their small guild becuase they dont want to be branded a loot whore or a traitor. So they log in everyday, power up their char, do nothing but exp in 2 year old dungeons work on AA points they wil never get full use of and eventually quit when they get fed up of it all. <br>
<br>
In answer to the topics question.  yeah some people use their middle tier guild as a stepping stone to a higher tier guild. On the other hand i see higher tier guilds use lower tier players as stepping stones for higher tier loot for their core members. .<br>
<br>
Look at some of the guild sites in the general forum and check out some of the rosters.  youll see a guild with x number of class and  really only one has any good gear.  The rest have very low tier loot and tend to quit sooner  than later becuase the loot hog of that class is taking everything for himself and the  little guy says *f this* quits and gets replaced by another little guy who gets the same treatment.  <br>
<br>
Its an endless circle and many people blindly play like it doesnt exist. i think thats much worse than when a player quits the guild after getting  an &quot;epic&quot; (omg you left after we gave you a 2 year old piece of loot. i hate you!).<br>
